<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Robert_Ballard.jpg" class="image" title="Robert D. Ballard"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/a/af/Robert_Ballard.jpg" width="220" height="324" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">Robert D. Ballard</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><b>Robert Duane Ballard</b> (born <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1942-06-30"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="06-30"><a href="/wiki/June_30" title="June 30">June 30</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1942" title="1942">1942</a></span> in <a href="/wiki/Wichita,_Kansas" title="Wichita, Kansas">Wichita, Kansas</a>) is a former <a href="/wiki/Commander_(United_States)" title="Commander (United States)">commander</a> in the <a href="/wiki/United_States_Navy" title="United States Navy">United States Navy</a> and an <a href="/wiki/Oceanography" title="Oceanography">oceanographer</a> who is most noted for his work in underwater <a href="/wiki/Archaeology" title="Archaeology">archaeology</a>. He is most famous for the discoveries of the wrecks of the <a href="/wiki/RMS_Titanic" title="RMS Titanic">RMS <i>Titanic</i></a> in 1985, the <a href="/wiki/German_battleship_Bismarck" title="German battleship Bismarck">battleship <i>Bismarck</i></a> in 1989, and the wreck of the aircraft carrier <a href="/wiki/USS_Yorktown_(CV-5)" title="USS Yorktown (CV-5)">USS <i>Yorktown</i></a> in 1998. Most recently he discovered the wreck of <a href="/wiki/John_F._Kennedy" title="John F. Kennedy">John F. Kennedy</a>'s <a href="/wiki/PT-109" title="PT-109" class="mw-redirect">PT-109</a> in 2003 and visited <a href="/wiki/Biuku_Gasa_and_Eroni_Kumana" title="Biuku Gasa and Eroni Kumana">the Solomon Islander natives</a> who saved its crew.</p>
